article.headline: Cal St.-Fullerton 106, Hope International 60
article.story: FULLERTON, Calif. -- Josh Akognon scored 25 points and made six of 11 shots from 3-point range to lead Cal State Fullerton's 106-60 rout of Hope International on Thursday night. Jacques Streeter added 13 points and 12 assists for the Titans (2-1). Gerard Anderson, Ray Miller and Chris Rhymes contributed 12 points apiece, as Fullerton shot 59.7 percent. Buai Tut scored 15 points for the Royals (0-2), an NAIA team that lost 26 of 27 games last season. Fullerton held a 22-18 lead before using a 17-2 surge to build a 39-20 advantage with 8:04 left in the first half. Hope International scored one point during a span of 6:15. The Titans led by 30 points at halftime and by as many as 52 late in the game.
